        <h2>Disaster Recovery</h2>
            <p>
Apogy cloud disaster recovery plan is designed to manage and test the steps required to move cloud services from the primary production cloud environment to a secondary cloud services environment in a separate and diverse location.
As daily backups of the primary cloud services environment are completed they are stored in the secondary cloud services environment so they can be utilized in the case of a disaster and are current within a 36-hour period.
            </p>
            <p>
When a disaster scenario occurs the Apogy cloud services environment will be re-deployed into the secondary cloud services environment using the same validated processes that were used during the deployment of the primary cloud services environment.  Customer will be functional within 24 hours of the disaster being identified. This plan is tested annually and results are recorded to identify potential improvement points.
            </p>
    </div>
