            <h2>Software Development and Testing Approach</h2>
            <p>
Apogy is a single-instance multi-tenant software-as-a-service application. As such, all new Apogy releases deployed to Apogy’ cloud services environment will provide customers instant access to the newest features and fixes. The product is released in a single-instance, iterative, date-bound fashion on a regular basis.  The frequency of these releases is yet to be determined, however it is likely that Apogy can support a 2 to 3-month major release interval, with between 4 and 6 iterative releases per year.
            </p>
            <p>
Apogy was created following standard Apogy SDLC policies and development procedures, using an agile approach to development and a continuous integration approach, with a daily build procedure generating each build and standard automated unit, integration, and regression tests executed to verify each component and interface, and to confirm success prior to further testing and development.  To keep Apogy is a fully verified state, Apogy runs every release of Apogy through a complete testing workflow prior to GA in accordance with an SDLC policy, testing procedures, and verification plans. This validation includes standard Installation, Operational, as well as Performance tests, user acceptance tests (UAT), and a third-party security assessment. A full set installation of operational and performance qualification tests are executed according to an approved plan against Apogy supported versions. Test results are summarized and a full set of evidence and traceability are gathered and verified by Quality Assurance.
            </p>
